                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="to"
                        >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-03T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Your 294, March 2, 11 a.m. If and when any notification is received with
                    regard to establishment of new regime in Manchuria, <pb facs="0600" n="496"
                        xml:id="pg_496"/> inform Department but take no additional action in absence
                    of Department’s further instructions.</p>
                <p>Instruct Mukden and Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
